From: Simon Desfarges <simonx.desfarges@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 2014 17:16:41 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 283/429] Power: Put MIO unit in D0i3

MIO is powered off.

Signed-off-by: Simon Desfarges <simonx.desfarges@intel.com>
---
 arch/x86/platform/intel-mid/pmu_tng.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/platform/intel-mid/pmu_tng.c b/arch/x86/platform/intel-mid/pmu_tng.c
index 063cfc437c88..fdb0dd651dc4 100644
--- a/arch/x86/platform/intel-mid/pmu_tng.c
+++ b/arch/x86/platform/intel-mid/pmu_tng.c
@@ -207,6 +207,8 @@ int pmu_set_power_state_tng(u32 reg_pm0, u32 si_mask, u32 ns_mask)
 static int __init pmu_nc_poweroff(void) {
 	/* Power off DPA */
 	pmu_set_power_state_tng (DSP_SS_PM, DPA_SSC, TNG_COMPOSITE_D3);
+	/* Power off MIO */
+	pmu_set_power_state_tng (MIO_SS_PM, MIO_SSC, TNG_COMPOSITE_D3);
 	return 0;
 }
 
